@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { * { animation: none !important; transition: none !important; } } as a global override. For JS-driven anim: window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches before triggering.

Why: vestibular disorders make non-essential motion painful. The OS-level toggle is the user's accessibility request — honouring it is non-negotiable for shipped apps.

When: any app with animation. Framer Motion's MotionConfig reducedMotion='user' wires this automatically.
